sources.description:
In a post nuclear Earth, survivors are stuck in a valley and have to protect themselves from cannibalistic mutant human beings, and each other in some cases.

Original title: In the Year 2889 AKA: The Day the World Ended (1967)
Director: Larry Buchanan
Writer: Harold Hoffman 
Stars: Paul Petersen, Quinn O'Hara, Charla Doherty
Genres: Classics, Cult, Horror, Sci-Fi , TV

Summary: A Devastating Nuclear Attack, Trapped Survivors, Stranded on the Way to California, Potential Dangers of Radiation Exposure, Isolation and Supernatural Occurrences, Responsibility Towards Humanity, Dwindling Supplies and Stronger Beings, Mysterious Situation and Potential Danger, Fear of a Creature and the Use of Water as a Weapon, The Commencement: A Tale of Survival and Uncertainty
